{"id":1176,"date":"2022-02-15T16:56:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-15T16:56:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1176"},"modified":"2022-02-14T12:57:17","modified_gmt":"2022-02-14T12:57:17","slug":"configure-systems-to-boot-into-a-specific-target-automatically","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1176","title":{"rendered":"Configure systems to boot into a specific target automatically"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve also gone over this in a previous <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=845\">post<\/a><\/strong>. So just the quick tldr.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>You can find what\u2019s your default target, by typing<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl get-default<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"712\" height=\"66\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?resize=640%2C59&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-847\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?w=712&amp;ssl=1 712w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?resize=300%2C28&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-138.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>And you can switch to one with<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo systemctl isolate multi-user.target<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And you will be immediately move into to the terminal<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"814\" height=\"274\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=640%2C215&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-848\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?w=814&amp;ssl=1 814w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=300%2C101&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=768%2C259&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-139.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>To change a default target, you use command<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">systemctl set-default graphical target<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also do this by interacting the&nbsp;<strong>GRUB bootloader<\/strong>. Just reboot or start your system, choose your OS and press e for editing the bootproces.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"708\" height=\"390\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?resize=640%2C353&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-849\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?w=708&amp;ssl=1 708w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?resize=24%2C13&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?resize=36%2C20&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-140.png?resize=48%2C26&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we simply add the sentence \u201c<strong>systemd.unit=multi-user.target<\/strong>\u201d to the end of the\u00a0<strong>\u201clinux line\u201d<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/lh3.googleusercontent.com\/69Y79-G5T50eqBIVpuqcsKekVjLZxzjEEr99EqAvyVmFjIuoHbu_ZwyLeBvoWUVGEZVzfLTmIHNz9eObCZkJW0wdlgOLxDcaeMPKAuNVcBKHiDA38pRv7IVzW9y2sJfEtUC4g9jN\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We&#8217;ve also gone over this in a previous post. So just the quick tldr. You [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1174,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[421,313,397,220,423],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/rhsa-Deploy-configure-and-maintain-systems-1.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1176"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_rout